description:
BIG thank you to the School of Visual Storytelling for sponsoring this video! http://svslearn.com/kelseyrodriguez. Artists don't need to starve, and I'm tired of people saying that modern artists "have" to become influencers in order to make a living. 

There are a TON of options out there for creative people. From becoming a textile designer, an in-house illustrator for a small company, or a prop artist/designer for an indie-production studio, there are OPTIONS out there for you. 

Just as an aside-- while I do mention movie poster work in this video, please respect the ongoing SAG-AFTRA and GWA strike by actors and writers, who are striking against major studios and seeking better pay and working conditions. They've asked content creators to refrain from promoting (even organically) stricken work.

description:

So, Threads launched last week. While I'm pretty sad about Twitter's painful and prolonged death (because let's be real, how can they come back from this?? there are new scandals EVERY WEEK) I'm also really conflicted about Thread's existence, and it's parent company: Meta. 

Twitter has been going downhill ever since Elon Musk purchased it last year, and the vibrant artistic community that used to live there is increasingly moving off-platform. So where are artists supposed to go next? Is Threads the next social media platform for artists and creative content creators? Let's talk about it.

description:
Let me know how what aspects of art you've been studying lately down in the comments :) Thank you as always to Squarespace for sponsoring the channel. Use code KELSEYRODRIGUEZ to get 10% off: https://squarespace.com/kelseyrodriguez

ğŸ’¬ JOIN OUR FREE DISCORD SERVER: https://discord.com/servers/the-studio-lounge-805831366406438912

Grisaille painting is something I've always wanted to try, and this past week I finally gave it a go! Grisaille painting is a technique where you do the first layers of your piece entirely in black and white, later using that underpainting as a guide when you begin to add color. You can either add color in glazes or as opaque layers, it's up to you! I tried both to see which one I preferred, and while glazing is pretty cool, it wasn't quite what I was going for. 

I really enjoy constantly pushing myself as an artist, trying new techniques and mediums and embracing life as a life-long learner. I consider myself a primarily self taught artist, and I'm aware I have a long way to go before I'll ever consider myself a master of the medium, but I really do enjoy the journey :)

description:
Marlene Vega has managed to take her art business part time with just her phone through the power of short form video content. Posting Instagram reels and short videos on TikTok has enabled her to take her passion into a profitable small business (!!!)

And the craziest thing? she manages to do all of this while working a regular 9 to 5. In this interview, we chat about time management, Instagram vs. TikTok vs. YouTube Shorts, how to get in the habit of filming, and so much more. Generally just everything related to social media strategy for artists :)

Short form video content is something a lot of artists have been resistant to incorporating into their marketing strategy, but it has the potential to take your business to the next level.

description:

It's been a rough few months, but I think things are finally looking up. I've been making more art, finding better work/life balance, recovering from my burnout/art block/imposter syndrome, and figuring out how I want to change my content going forward.

description:
AI art has been taking the art world by storm, so let's talk about it. This is a super controversial issue, but one absolutely worth discussing. 

I think the reality is that AI will have transformational effects on virtually every single industry, NOT just art. This technology will be regulated over time, but that doesn't mean that it won't affect us. Unfortunately, there's just no putting the toothpaste back in the tube, we have to learn how to adapt our art careers. 

For those of you super worried: I think it's far from a foregone conclusion that every creative job will be wiped out. There are TONS of lawsuits currently being litigated on this topic.

video_name: Do THIS instead of going to art school
user_tags: ['new masters academy', 'learn art online', 'full time artist income', 'how to become a full time artist', 'art career', 'how to launch an art career', 'income streams for artists', 'art career goals', 'self taught artist', 'productivity for artists', 'business tips for artists', 'entrepreneurship for artists', 'art fundamentals study vlog', 'marketing for artists', 'diy an art degree', 'self taught artist tips']
description:
I've talked to so many professional artists and the consensus is this: you DO NOT need to go to a traditional 4-year college and pursue an art degree to succeed either on your own OR in the industry. You can DIY your art degree for a FRACTION of the price. 

One such example (yes they are sponsoring this video, yes I do genuinely like them) is New Master's Academy: https://www.nma.art/?ref=137 . They have the best catalog of fine arts courses, from everything to animation, concept art, anatomy fundamentals, and oil painting (my personal drug of choice)

A sufficiently determined and motivated person could get all the value of art school and more just with the resources available to you on the internet for free, but almost anyone could find a comparable education for FAR cheaper than the cost of a traditional art degree with a combination of independent paid courses, art books, etc. 

ğŸ“š My art book collection: https://bookshop.org/lists/my-art-book-collection

THAT BEING SAID - before you try to eviscerate me in the comments, art school is GREAT for some people!!!! Some people need that structure! But some people don't want to be saddled with tens of thousands of dollars, if not well past six figures, of student loan debt. I have friends that are incredibly thankful they went, but it isn't for everyone. I want to present people with as much information as possible so they can make the decision that's best for them.

description:
Did you ever want to download your Youtube videos in HD but you're only using the free version? No worries, let me show you how to download Youtube videos on iPhone in 2023!

Let's begin by opening the "Youtube" app.
Next, tap on your profile icon at the top-right corner of the screen, then click "Settings". Select the "Offline" button.
Lastly, tap the "Download quality" and set your desired resolution, Let's set it to "10-80 p, Full HD".
Now go to the youtube video that you want to download, press the 3 dot icon at the bottom part of the youtube video. Tap on "Download video" once downloading is done, you can now watch your youtube video in HD offline!

Let's start with Step #1. Pick a Profitable Niche

I've been promoting this niche ever since I started my blog and my online business. I'm talking about hosting providers. 
When you build a website, you need a place to host all your information. My site is anastasiablogger.com and the first $700 I ever made with this site about 5 years ago when I just started making money online, was my affiliate commissions promoting a hosting provider. 
This is a very profitable niche because you can get paid anywhere from $50 and more per client you refer. 
And since all of us need hosting to start a website, we all have an experience using one provider or another and we can certainly recommend these services to people we know or even create a page on your site with tools or resources that you use and mention your hosting provider there. 

Now the next step is to Find the Best Affiliate Program in this niche.

There are many hosting providers and it's hard to pick the one you want to promote. 
I can tell you that you should look at certain factors when you decide. 
Of course, the commission you'll be paid matters but it's not the only factor. 
You also want to recommend a hosting provider that has great reviews.
If you recommend a hosting that users regret buying, you might soon find that people are not happy with the services and if often they cancel their plans, then your commissions will be cancelled as well.

So the affiliate program from Cloudways is a combination of two things - great reviews and great commissions.

There's something truly special about hitting that first $100,000 mark. It's like a switch flips in your life. 
Every financial goal you set, whether it's $500,000, or even 10 million, somehow seems to come easier once you've bagged your first hundred grand.
But how do you get to that initial milestone? 
That's what I'm going to show you in this video. 7 different ways you can start working towards your first life-changing financial goal.

I know how it feels to have next to nothing. Not too long ago, I had less than $5,000 in savings and was working at a sole-sucking corporate job. 

A few years later, I made over half a million dollars online before taxes. 
But what I really want you to get, and I stress this because it's the absolute truth, is that I'm just like you. The things I've achieved, you can too, probably even more. And the first task on that journey? Earning your first $100,000 online 

The first way you can try is 

#1. Method 1 - Affiliate Marketing 

Affiliate marketing, if done right, is indeed a relatively easy and fast way to earn money online. Here's why:
No Need to Create a Product: you don't need to invest time and money in creating a product or service, you simply promote things made by others. 
Passive Income Potential: Once you've set up your affiliate links and started driving traffic to them, you can earn money 24/7. Even when you're sleeping, on vacation, or spending time with family, your affiliate links can generate sales.
No Customer Service: Since you're not the one selling the product or service, you don't have to worry about customer requests, complaints, or returns. The company whose products you're promoting takes care of all that.

To start with this method, you can register on a couple of large affiliate networks. My personal favorite is called Impact, I recently made there about $5000 in commissions. You can join them using my link anastasiablogger.com/impact

What the heck is going on with Pinterest Idea pins? Are they dead? I had to make an entire investigation and I'll tell you what I found so far and what's going to happen with Idea pins.
Pinterest rolled out a HUGE update but it doesn't look the same for all users yet! I asked in my FB group for my Pinterest program members, and from their answers I understand that most of the users in the United States and in some other countries can no longer create Idea pins. The update seems to go out quite randomly country-wise. I've got screenshots from a user in Taiwan and in India and Australia who have the same interface as users in the United States. I live in Portugal and my interface has changed but it still is not yet to the same final update.
So you know what? Just go to your Pinterest account, click Create, and see which options you get. On my account, I still have the option to Create Idea pins. What has changed for me is that I now also can add a link URL to an Idea pin as well as a pin title and description. Previously, we didn't have a field for a link on Idea pins.
And on this screenshot another user shared with me, you'll see the new interface after the full update. Wait what?  There is no option to add an Idea pin at all!
I thought they just added links to Idea pins but now it looks like there are NO Idea pins anymore. What about the old Idea pins that took us so much time to create? Are they gone too? Let's find out!
Let's do a quick survey to know what Pinterest is really up to! Check this out on your account and let me know in the comments below where you live and if you still can create Idea pins or not anymore. And how do your old Idea pins show up if your account has been updated?
But if we like to look for some good news out of this confusing updateâ€¦ We can at least add links to our old Idea pins!
By the way, a quick pro tip - and I honestly hope I deserve a like on my video for this one! 
Open your Pinterest Analytics, apply the filter to see only Idea pins, change the dates for the longest period available and you'll get the list of your top-performing old Idea pins. 
What I suggest that you do is click Edit at least on your TOP-10 best Idea pins and see what we can do here. We can add links to our old pins! 
Since these pins are outperforming other Idea pins on our account and they've been doing it for many months, it's worth the effort to go back and add links to these old Idea pins!
Now go ahead and give me a thumbs up if you think it's a good idea! Also, Subscribe and hit the bell button to get more of my videos in your feed! 
Pinterest published in their Newsroom a confusing announcement about his update. They said they are introducing an easier way to create pins - all types of pins will now have a unified flow instead of the different flows we used to have for Image pins, Video pins and Idea pins. 
And they showed this example of an account that has only one button - Create a Pin and no option to create Idea pins.
So if this is in their Newsroom, I assume this change will be slowly rolled out to all the accounts around the world.
On the bright side, you should know that your old Idea pins will still remain on the platform, and as I mentioned, you can now even go back to your top Idea pins and add links to your website from them.

And the first thing you need to do to get Pinterest traffic is
Make Sure that Users CAN Save Something from Your Website
When you look into your Pinterest analytics, you want to see a ton of Other Pins. 
See I have mostly Other pins in my top 10 pins, and my account gets 10+ Million monthly viewers on Pinterest. 
What does this Others even mean? It means that YOUR account did not create those pins but they are still pins linked to your website. So these are other people saving images from YOUR site.
You probably don't realize HOW important those OTHER pins are because well maybe you have never even seen them in your stats. Maybe your account is new or you never had any popular Other pins.
 
But I am fortunate because I have seen the analytics not only on my own Pinterest accounts but also of dozens or maybe hundreds Pinterest accounts of my 1:1 clients by now. 


And you know what I noticed? All the accounts that do really GREAT on Pinterest that I've seen, always have a ton of pins marked as Others!  And usually, very few pins marked as their own pins, ever popup in at the top of their Pinterest stats.


Here's how these Others pins appear in your Pinterest analytics. 
Say, someone found your pin on Pinterest, they clicked on it to visit your website. 
On the site, they thought your page was so great that they decided to save it to a board on THEIR Pinterest account. They can use a button like this for social sharing on your site and save an image as a pin linked to your page. But that happen only IF any image is available on your page for saving. 

If you open any pin that's marked as Others, Pinterest doesn't show you right away to which particular board this pin was saved but you can track it if you open detailed analytics on that pin, then you will click here and can see all the boards to which other users saved this pin.
So 3 things can go wrong with Other pins, and can limit the amount of traffic you will get from Pinterest. 
I noticed that in many cases, people create Pinterest-optimized vertical pin images just to save them on Pinterest linked to their website.

Today we will about how you can make some serious cash using Pinterest. You heard it right - Pinterest isn't just a place for recipes and home decor, it's a goldmine for making money! You'll see how you can make a six-figure income using Pinterest.
Let's get into it!

Selling Print-on Demand Products

This is a great opportunity for those who are creative and have a talent for designing unique and eye-catching designs.
So, how does it work? Well, you can create designs for a variety of products like t-shirts, mugs, phone cases, and more. 
You don't have to worry about the production process as there are several print-on-demand platforms out there like Printful, Printify, Redbubble, Teespring, and Zazzle that handle everything from printing to shipping.
All you have to do is create your designs, upload them to the platform of your choice, and then promote them on Pinterest. You can create beautiful pins that showcase your designs and link them directly to your product pages. With the right targeting and promotion, you can reach a wide audience and generate sales.
The great thing about selling print-on-demand products is that there is no upfront cost or inventory to manage. 
You can create designs in your free time and upload them to the platform whenever you want. Plus, you can earn passive income from your designs as people continue to purchase them.
When you promote your products on Pinterest, the platform gives great additional features for eCommerce stores:

In this video I'm going to give you guys a step-by-step tutorial on how to run Pinterest ads and see here I'm able to get traffic to my offers anywhere between 10 to 20 cents per click. I'll show you how. 
And before we can make the campaign we want to make sure that  you use a Pinterest business account
You have installed Pinterest tag on your website to track page visits, purchases and so on. 

When you have your Pinterest tag on the site, it helps Pinterest collect data about the users who click on your promoted pins, and to optimize your campaigns so that you can get more sales at a lower budget. 

All you need to do is click on Ads then Conversions, and from here if you already have a verified domain, Pinterest will give you a few suggestions based on the system you use on your website.

Here, you can select your objective and budget, which are the first things you need to do. Your objective will depend on your niche and goals, but it will likely fall into one of three categories: building awareness, driving consideration, or getting conversions. 
Building Awareness objective will basically show your ads to a maximum number of people on Pinterest. These ads can help you reach new audiences who may not have heard of your business before. 
But that doesn't always necessarily mean you'll get the best ratio of clicks per impression with ads. So if your goal is to drive more visitors to your site, then you should use a Consideration campaign. It used to be called Traffic campaign so that explained even better what it gives you. 
 
So in this case I have verified a Wordpress blog so you see the options I've got are Google Tag Manager, Worpdress itself and WooCommerce. 
If you verified a Shopify store for example, the options for you would be different.

Probably one of the hottest online business models to come up over the past year or two is affiliate marketing. But to be honest, even I was REALLY confused about what it exactly is. 

So today Iâ€™ll be talking about what affiliate marketing is for beginners and tips on how YOU can get started making money with it today.

What is affiliate marketing? Well, itâ€™s basically just getting paid for referrals. You get a commission for getting a user to take some sort of action, usually a purchase or a sign up.

How does affiliate marketing work? You choose something youâ€™re going to market, and you get your audience to see it, then take an action

What can you do affiliate marketing for? Just about anything! The main ones are products, services, software, or digital products. It really depends on the topic of your content. 

Is it really passive? For the most part, yes! Once you get things set up, and you get some traffic rolling in, it CAN be passive. But up until that point, not so passive.

How much money can you make doing affiliate marketing? As much or as little as you want to! The sky is pretty much the limit when it comes to affiliate marketing. My first month with Siteground I did $200 in affiliates, and on average do anywhere between $200-300 a month in Amazon Associates alone.

How much money does it take to get started with affiliate marketing? That depends, but the minimum amount to start is $0! Yes, you can start this kind of online business for free, totally possible. But, you can also put money into the business to start, anywhere between $100-$1500 bucks.

Step #1, pick your topic/niche. Similar to starting a blog/youtube channel/podcast etc, you need a target niche when doing affiliate marketing. Why? Because you need to know what kind of content to produce and what kind of products/services to market.

Step #2 is to figure out what youâ€™re going to market. You might be doing products or services or software or courses, whatever it might be, you just have to know what youâ€™re going to do.

Step #3 is, create a marketing platform. If youâ€™re trying to do some affiliate marketing without putting ANY money into your business (and Iâ€™m assuming here you have at least a smartphone and internet access) you can create an Instagram account, Facebook page, even a YouTube channel (or all 3!).

If youâ€™re willing to put a very minimal amount into your new business, I HIGHLY recommend starting a website. Why? You OWN it, youâ€™re not depended on another already built platform. For hosting, I recommend Siteground (check it out here: http://bit.ly/2JjtgOE)
Step 4 is to build your audience & earn their trust! Whether you're blogging, on YouTube, Instagram, whatever, you need to get people to TRUST YOU to make this a viable business strategy.

Step 5 is to start making your 10x content to start making your 10x money. But just because youâ€™re trying to get them to convert doesnâ€™t mean you need to be super spammy with your content.

Step 6 is to throw in the pitch. Now donâ€™t just come out and blast them with the pitch. If youâ€™ve created 10x content and built their trust over time, just drop how you use the product or service and totally recommend it. Your trust and content should really take care of the rest.

Step #7 is to repeat steps 4-6! 

So thatâ€™s what affiliate marketing is and how you do it! Hopefully this video has helped you understand affiliate marketing better and get you on your way to start making money.

Overview of basic usages of subdomains:

Subdomains are a way to create separate sections or parts of a website, each with its own unique web address or URL. Here are some common uses of subdomains:

Separate content: You can use subdomains to separate different types of content on your website. For example, you could use a subdomain for your blog, e-commerce store, or forum.

Testing and development: Subdomains can also be useful for testing new website features or for developing a new website. You can create a subdomain and use it as a sandbox or staging environment without affecting the live website.

Language versions: If you have a global audience, you may want to create subdomains for different language versions of your website. For example, you could use a subdomain for your French website and another for your German website.

Mobile versions: If you have a mobile version of your website, you can use a subdomain to separate it from your desktop version. For example, you could use "m.yourdomain.com" for your mobile site.

Branding: Subdomains can also be used for branding purposes. For example, a company might use a subdomain for their blog, such as "blog.companyname.com" to reinforce their brand identity.

Overall, subdomains are a useful tool for organizing and separating different sections of a website. By using subdomains, you can create a more organized and user-friendly website for your visitors.

How you can be benefited with subdomains as a freelancer?

As a freelancer, using subdomains can be a great way to organize and promote your work online. Here are a few ways subdomains can be used:

Portfolio: Create a subdomain for your portfolio to showcase your work to potential clients. This will make it easy for them to find and view your best work all in one place.

Services: Use a subdomain to highlight your services and offerings. This can help potential clients understand what you do and how you can help them.

Blog: If you maintain a blog to promote your work, consider using a subdomain for it. This can help with SEO and make it easier for readers to find your content.

Testimonials: If you've received positive feedback from clients, create a subdomain to feature those testimonials. This can help build trust and credibility with potential clients.

Landing pages: If you're running a marketing campaign, use a subdomain for your landing page. This can help you track traffic and conversions for that specific campaign.

Overall, using subdomains can help you organize and promote your work online, making it easier for potential clients to find and hire you.

description:
Hire a Freelancer to Fix Excluded by NOINDEX Google Search Console Issues: https://rafys.net/fiverr

Fixing Google Search Console errors are really important to keep your website look fresh and help google index your website easily. In this video, I have shown 2 Ways to Fix Excluded by NOINDEX tag in #googlesearchconsole 

In Google Search Console, the "Excluded by 'noindex' tag" error message indicates that some of the pages on your website have been excluded from the index by the "noindex" directive. This error can occur if you have inadvertently added the "noindex" tag to pages that you want to be indexed or if you have intentionally added it to pages that should not be indexed.

To fix this error, you will need to identify which pages on your website have been excluded by the "noindex" tag and determine whether or not they should be indexed. If you have intentionally added the "noindex" tag to some pages, you will need to remove it to ensure that these pages can be indexed and appear in search results.

On the other hand, if you have inadvertently added the "noindex" tag to pages that you want to be indexed, you will need to remove the tag and resubmit the pages for indexing using Google Search Console. To do this, you can follow these steps:

1. Use Yoast SEO or Rankmath on your website and find the pages or blog posts which has noindex tag, and enable the index option.

2. Find out the pages and prefixes on Google Search Console and add them in removal request.

Once you have made the necessary changes, resubmit the page for indexing using the "Request indexing" feature in Google Search Console.

In summary, the "Excluded by 'noindex' tag" error in Google Search Console indicates that some of your website's pages have been excluded from search engine indexing. To fix this error, you will need to identify the affected pages, determine whether they should be indexed or not, remove the "noindex" tag if necessary, and resubmit the pages for indexing using Google Search Console.

description:

Fame? Views? Wealth? Designer tags? Family? Follower counts?

This looks completely different for everyone.  For us, it's been one of those things that have drastically changed over the years..

For the longest time, so many of our own feelings around success were wrapped up in views, wealth, and comparing our story with the story of others (especially on social media).  It was almost like social media was seeping into real life..

I mean how can it not? When you consume social media allllll the time, it's honestly hard comparing yourself to the picture perfect influencer, with a big house..fancy car and designer everything.  Social comparison triggers those insecurities we all have, and can make you feel inferior or inadequate.

In today's podcast, Doug and I talk about what our definition of success is NOW and how it's evolved over time.

With this new definition of success, we are more confident than ever that our lives will be fulfilled and meaningful.

3. ProfitÂ 
Youâ€™ve got the foundations in place and the content on autopilotâ€¦ and now youâ€™re ready to crank up the heat and be compensated for your hard work. Youâ€™ll learn multiple ways to make money (instead of just one!)Â properly pitch (and land) brand deals, set up affiliate links, create digital products, and sell online coursesâ€¦ regardless of your follower count and previous experience.

description:
Whatâ€™s been holding you back? If youâ€™ve been wanting to become a Content Creator but youâ€™ve been held back by fear or that little voice that tells you â€œyou canâ€™tâ€ itâ€™s time to let that go.Â 

I found this quote in my fortune cookie the other day and I wanted to share it with you:Â 

â€œItâ€™s easier to go down a hill than to go up, but the view is much better at the top.â€Â 

If Iâ€™ve learned one thing the past few years, itâ€™s that the Content Creator journey is far from linear. 

But lately, I feel like Iâ€™ve been seeing a lot of people feeling like just giving up completely. ğŸ˜…Â 

And I get it - these platforms are NOT making it easy on us.Â 

Surprise! Another new feature released - or hey, letâ€™s throw out another entire new app while weâ€™re at it!

And mix in an algorithm that can seem to make up its mind (a photo app - sike, VIDEO now - but not too much videoâ€¦ actually letâ€™s switch it to photos with TEXTâ€¦ ğŸ¥´).Â 

Itâ€™s exhausting to say the least.Â 

And itâ€™s natural to want to throw in the towel when nothing seems to be going your way and everyday feels like an uphill battle, thinkingâ€¦ â€œwhere the HECK is the top?!â€Â 

While this can be the hardest part about entrepreneurship, I have to admitâ€¦ itâ€™s also one of my favorite parts.Â 

Because that quote rings true - the view at the top really is so much better than anything I couldâ€™ve dreamed.Â 

Of course, Iâ€™m still climbing my own mountains, but I have a feeling the moment you want to give up is right before the moment the clear clouds clear and it all becomes worth it.

So let's just agree to ignore that little voice that tells you â€œyou canâ€™tâ€ today.

Follow your joy ğŸ§¡

description:
You might not want to be posting all about âœ¨youâœ¨ all the time...

If all of your content is focused on yourself, like: 

"What I eat in a day..."
"Day in my life..."
"This is how I do this..."
"This is how I do that..."

You may lose some of your viewers! Instead, make sure to also include selfless content. Focus on using the words "you", "your" and "yours."

"Warm-ups YOU should be doing"
"How you can do xyz"

This helps pull the user in to help them feel like the content is for them!!

video_name: 3 things that tripled my sales ğŸ’¸ 1
user_tags: ['digital product academy', 'digital products', 'etsy', 'make money online', 'online business', 'passive income', 'shopify', 'shruti pangtey', 'side hustle ideas', 'side hustles']
description:
3 things that tripled my sales ğŸ’¸

1. Focusing on traffic generating platforms 

While it is tempting to be everywhere, I audited which platforms were performing best for us. 

Once I knew which platforms these were I focused ONLY on creating content on these and repurposed everywhere else. 

Now what works for me might not work for every one else but personally I love making videos so I knew that had to be my main way of creating content. 

2. Created offers for various stages of the customer journey

The truth is not everyone is ready to or willing to invest in your most high end amazing offers - even if those bring the maximum transformation. 

I asked my audience questions and looked at what problems they were facing and then created products that solved those problems. 

It sounds sooo easy when you put it this way but that is literally what every good business does. Figure out what problem to solve and then solve it really well. 

3. Worked on my mindset and fear of showing up 

I looked at people who were way ahead of me and looked at what their beliefs were. I studied people I admired, read the same books, listened to meditations, put myself in a mindfulness retreat and worked on flipping my mindset. 

The biggest personal block I worked on was my fear of showing up and being â€œseenâ€ as massively successful. 

I stopped putting a limit on what my income should look like month to month and just focused on what my desired life should look like. 

i literally do not fuss about metrics anymore and its such a relief to stop caring - instead of acting from a place of fear I act from a place of self confidence. I know that I can always bounce back no matter what. Life is not a linear journey - and neither is business. 

When faced with making decisions in my business, I ask myself, what would someone who is 10x ahead do right now? 

I love growth. i love new challenges and once I reprogrammed my brain to see and feel abundant 24*7, there really was a massive shift. 

Ready to work on your digital product journey and follow my roadmap? Comment â€œreadyâ€ to get my step by step course! ğŸ“²

video_name: Canva Logo Usage: What's allowed?
Canva Sellers ğŸ›‘ Can you use the Canva logo on your product images to sell templates?
user_tags: ['how to create canva templates', 'canva templates', 'how to sell canva templates', 'design with canva', 'canva for beginners', 'how to sell canva templates on etsy', 'canva tutorials', 'canva templates to sell on etsy', 'canva templates for sale', 'canva templates for etsy', 'canva templates tutorial', 'canva sellers', 'Can you use the Canva logo', 'sell canva templates', 'product images for templates', 'selling digital products on etsy', 'how to make canva templates to sell on etsy', "can't use canva logo"]
description:
Canva Sellers ğŸ›‘ Can you use the Canva logo on your product images to sell templates?

Yesterday a response from Canva regarding the use of their logos on marketing material (such a product images) was passed on to us stating (screenshot featured in the video):

Please note that using "Canva" as part of a trademark (business name or logo) or a product name is not permitted. However if the use of "Canva" in the name is descriptive and not the main feature (example: ABC Teaches Canva), such use is allowed.

In addition, we're more than happy for the Canva name to be referred to descriptively in content. However, any reference to the Canva name must be in plain text (not using any stylized version of the Canva name or the Canva logos) and the reference must be informational or descriptive in nature. This means you can only refer to the Canva name to describe Canva as a product or service, and using the Canva name commercially or otherwise as a brand identifier is not permitted.

---
So what does this mean for sellers?
To summarize, using the logo on your thumbnails to promote and drive traffic to Canva is not allowed - the only use would be a descriptive note such as 'editable in Canva', in a plain font not using the logo.

video_name: Don't Sell These Books on Amazon. DO THIS INSTEAD And Make $8,000+ Per Month (Passive Income)
user_tags: ['passive income', 'side hustle', 'amazon', 'amazon kdp', 'amazon fba', 'how to make money online', 'digital products']
description:

video_name: Is Velocity Banking Strategy a SCAM? - Expert Proves It Doesn't Work
user_tags: ['velocity banking', 'velocity banking strategy', 'velocity banking explained', 'pay down debt faster', 'pay off your debt faster', 'debt snowball', 'debt snowball method', 'debt avalanche', 'debt avalanche method', 'personal finance', 'debt consolidation', 'william lee', 'think wealthy velocity banking', 'dave ramsey', 'suze orman', 'vanntastic!', 'vanntastic velocity banking', 'vanntastic finance', 'velocity channel']
description:
Velocity Banking Strategy is supposedly a way to pay down debt faster by doing debt consolidation using a revolving credit line like a Home Equity Line of Credit (HELOC) or a credit card. However, in many cases, the Velocity Banking strategy doesn't work. This video is velocity banking explained: I explain and demonstrate why using velocity banking could take longer to pay off your debt and cost you more in interest expenses. Velocity banking almost certainly will not work to pay down debt faster when you are using a higher interest rate revolving loan to pay down a lower interest rate term loan. It might work if you can use a lower interest rate revolving loan to pay down higher interest rate term loan. However, it is less common for someone who is burdened by a high rate term loan to be able to get a lower rate revolving loan.... which is why I make the general statement that Velocity Banking Doesn't Work.  This is an important topic in personal finance. Watch the video to see the actual math for several scenarios. People interested in the debt snowball method and the debt avalanche method will find this useful, too. Check out some of the videos from Vanntastic finance, Velocity Channel, Suze Ormon and Dave Ramsey for other opinions on the topic. Some agree with me, some don't. I showed my math in full detail.

Your host in this video has been the CFO of several software companies and offers a lifetime of business experience to his audience. video_name: Is Velocity Banking Strategy a SCAM? - Expert Proves It Doesn't Work
user_tags: ['velocity banking', 'velocity banking strategy', 'velocity banking explained', 'pay down debt faster', 'pay off your debt faster', 'debt snowball', 'debt snowball method', 'debt avalanche', 'debt avalanche method', 'personal finance', 'debt consolidation', 'william lee', 'think wealthy velocity banking', 'dave ramsey', 'suze orman', 'vanntastic!', 'vanntastic velocity banking', 'vanntastic finance', 'velocity channel']
description:
Velocity Banking Strategy is supposedly a way to pay down debt faster by doing debt consolidation using a revolving credit line like a Home Equity Line of Credit (HELOC) or a credit card. However, in many cases, the Velocity Banking strategy doesn't work. This video is velocity banking explained: I explain and demonstrate why using velocity banking could take longer to pay off your debt and cost you more in interest expenses. Velocity banking almost certainly will not work to pay down debt faster when you are using a higher interest rate revolving loan to pay down a lower interest rate term loan. It might work if you can use a lower interest rate revolving loan to pay down higher interest rate term loan. However, it is less common for someone who is burdened by a high rate term loan to be able to get a lower rate revolving loan.... which is why I make the general statement that Velocity Banking Doesn't Work.  This is an important topic in personal finance. Watch the video to see the actual math for several scenarios. People interested in the debt snowball method and the debt avalanche method will find this useful, too. Check out some of the videos from Vanntastic finance, Velocity Channel, Suze Ormon and Dave Ramsey for other opinions on the topic. Some agree with me, some don't. I showed my math in full detail.

Your host in this video has been the CFO of several software companies and offers a lifetime of business experience to his audience. Will has an undergraduate degree in Economics, an MBA in finance from Cornell University, earned the CFA charter (Chartered Financial Analyst), and has worked as an equity research analyst at top Wall Street firms in addition to his experience running entrepreneurial companies.

Are you looking for inspiration on how to grow your business in a crowded market?

Look no further than Happilo, a premium gourmet brand for dry fruits and healthy snacking. Founded by Vikas D Nahar with just â‚¹10,000, Happilo has grown into a 500 crore revenue business, despite operating in a highly unorganized segment of the FMCG space.

In this video, we present to you Happiloâ€™s business case study and explore how Vikas leveraged multiple pivots, creative ad campaigns, and a laser focus on brand equity to achieve success. We cover how he identified pain-points in the market, pivoted his product line to offer more variety and improved shelf-life, and entered the offline omnichannel space to build a strong retail and distribution network.

Happilo's branding strategy includes a mix of Above the Line (ATL) and Below the Line (BTL) activations. By partnering with Rajasthan Royals as a title sponsor for IPL, the brand positioned itself as a healthy alternative for guilt-free snacking for cricket fans. Happilo's Diwali campaign with Bollywood stars Sid Malhotra and Kiara Advani helped the brand tap into the movie-going audience and add XP points to the association factor in building brand equity.

By keeping brand equity at the core of their business, Happilo has been able to capture a 20% share in the organized Dry Fruits market in a short span of time. Will the brand achieve international status as a homegrown Dry Fruits brand? Will Happilo become synonymous with healthy snacking among young adults? Only time will tell.

description:
Come with me while I make some cheap and easy oat milk! If you are gluten free, just make sure to get GF oats (which you probably already know). Here's the "recipe":

HOMEMADE OAT MILK
* 1 cup rolled oats
* 4 cups iced water
* blend for 15-30 seconds
* strain in fine mesh nut bag
* it's ready for consumption! My kids like it with cereal, I like to use it in my chocolate smoothie breakfast bowl (yes, those are as good as they sound).
